    "comment": "Rationale: Using immunocytochemistry and electron microscopy, the referenced study established that in the rat prelimbic prefrontal cortex, most 5-HT2a receptors are located within postsynaptic structures, predominantly on proximal and distal dendritic shafts. 5-HT2a receptor immunoreactivity was observed in 325 identifiable structures. Of these, 73% were postsynaptic profiles that were composed of either dendritic shafts (58%) or dendritic spine heads and necks (42%).\n\n21/11/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Four naive adult male Sprague-Dawley rats (Hilltop Laboratory Animals, Scottsdale, PA, USA) were used...",
